properties.name: Bar Celona
properties.description: Posted by BaobotOld Pasadena, Pasadena, CA, United StatesA modern Spanish Tapas Bar, Restaurant and late-night Lounge in the historic Colorado Boulevard retail district of Old Pasadena, is the creation of local entrepeneur Jack Huang. Combining a lively, casual and eclectic sophisticated atmosphere featuring live music, flamenco dancing and late-night DJ\'s with soaring contemporary, architectural design. Set on a stage of rich crimson and hues of mellow mustard, Bar Celona invokes the traditions of the Tapas Bars of Spain, with handcrafted murals of \'the running of the bulls\', wine offerings geared toward those of the Spanish vineyards, house made sangrias, and the popular small plates that trigger a smiling sign of memory in those that have traveled these foreign lands.

properties.name: Huntington Library, Art Collection & Botanical Gardens
properties.description: Posted by Kchristieh     1151 Oxford Road, San Marino, CA 91108World-class botanical gardens includes cactus garden, Australian garden, Japanese garden, roses, herbs, Shakespeare garden and much more. Chinese garden coming soon! The tearoom (reservations recommended) is wonderful, though not as charming as it was before Sodexho took it over. (My advice: Dim the lights! Put some music on!) Great art collection, library (for scholars) and gift shop. A wonderful way to spend a relaxing day. Visiting this convinced me that Southern California was actually a pretty place the first time I saw it over 20 years ago. Don\'t miss the new Children\'s Garden, even if you don\'t have kids. It\'s full of whimsical plants and water creations.

properties.name: William S. Hart County Park
properties.description: Posted by Renaistre   From the park website: "The former home and ranch of William S. Hart, silent film cowboy star and director. The Museum sits atop a hill within a large park area." Aside from the museum, the park grounds are home to a barnyard area with various animals, a gift shop, large shady lawns and picnic areas, and Hart Hall which can be rented for events such as weddings or small concerts.
